                "<b>We are learning [a scriptural connection between] \"strike\" and \"strike\":</b> Even though the verses are not similar, we are learning a scriptural connection (<i>gezera shava</i>), as was taught in the House of Rabbi Yishmael (Eruvin 51a), \"and the Priest came and the Priest left\" [wherein the connection is made even though the two phrases are dissimilar]. And [the phrase], \"whoever strikes a man,\" that we learned here, it is [just the word (or concept)] \"strike\" that was meant, and it was learned from [the verse], \"If a man injures his neighbor,\" since an injury comes from a strike. "
